{"lemma":"مَطْوِيٍّ","slug":"مَطْوِيٍّ","root":"ط.#.#","root_slug":"ط-_-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-_-_","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27395","n27396","n27397"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B7%D9%92%D9%88%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8D%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fold, flap, plica"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"winder for thread, a thing upon which spun thread is wound, or a board around which one rolls, folding-stick"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"switchblade, jackknife, penknife"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27395","headword_ar":"مَطْوًى","root":"TwY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"; and its pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTaAwK","text_ar":"مَطَاوٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and as a prefixed n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTaAwiY","text_ar":"مَطَاوِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaY~N","text_ar":"طَىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in five places."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTowFY","text_ar":"مَطْوًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be used as an inf. n., meaning The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"folding"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a garment, or piece of cloth: and as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of folding"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof: and signifies also the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inside"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof. (Har p. 160.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27396","headword_ar":"مِطْوًى","root":"TwY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A winder for thread;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing upon which spun thread is wound."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  And, as a word used by the vulgar, [but by them generally pronounced"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTowaY","text_ar":"مَطْوَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h, and without tenween,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A small"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clasp-"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knife."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n27397","headword_ar":"مَطْوِىٌّ","root":"TwY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Folded, folded up,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"folded together,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rolled up:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see 1, first sentence. ―         -b2-  And hence, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Made compact,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though folded; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"round,"},{"kind":"text","text":"like a scroll]. You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN maTowiy~apu","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ مَطْوِيَّةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxaloqi","text_ar":"الخَلْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mkr","text_ar":"مكر"},{"kind":"text","text":") [meaning, accord. to the PS in that art., (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A plump woman;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the same seems to be indicated by what immediately follows it in the S itself: but it is more correctly rendered (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a woman compacted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rounded, in make:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwiYa jisomuhu","text_ar":"طُوِىَ جِسْمُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". It may, however, signify also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A woman lean, lank,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slender, in make;"},{"kind":"text","text":"lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered lean,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawaAhu","text_ar":"طَوَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biy^orN maTowiy~apN","text_ar":"بِيْرٌ مَطْوِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A well cased"},{"kind":"text","text":"with stones [or with baked bricks]. (TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@ls~am`waAtu","text_ar":"وَا@لسَّمٰوَاتُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTowiy~aAtN biyamiynihi","text_ar":"مَطْوِيَّاتٌ بِيَمِينِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [xxxix. 67, generally understood to mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the heavens"},{"kind":"text","text":"shall be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"folded together,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rolled up, by his right hand"},{"kind":"text","text":"], has been expl. as meaning [that they shall be]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"destroyed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so says Er-Rághib. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}